title: FNV Game of the Week: Tigers rally to beat the Braves
text:
FNV Game of the Week: Tigers rally to beat the Braves Oscar Smith 15, Indian River 14: Extra Highlights Post to Facebook FNV Game of the Week: Tigers rally to beat the Braves Oscar Smith 15, Indian River 14: Extra Highlights  //on.wvec.com/1RADW8P   FNV Game of the Week: Tigers rally to beat the Braves Brian K Smith , 13News Now 1:44 a.m. EDT October 11, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Oscar Smith preserved its Southeastern District win streak to 79 in a row as they edged out Indian River 15-14. The game was held at Hickory High School in Chesapeake because of the expected large crowd. They weren't disappointed as the Braves jumped out to a 14-2 advantage care of a Tyre Givers-Wilson touchdown pass to Kyren Best touchdown pass from 40 yards. The Tigers rallied late and tied the game on a Deangelo White punt return of 59 yards. Kameron Luster got the extra point for the win.
